# Int4 overflow tests

(tx 'create schema test')
(tx 'create table test.item(field: int4)')
!tx 'insert (2147483648) into test.item (field)'
---
> error[PO0001]: value overflows column `field` type `INT4`
>   1 │ insert (2147483648) into test.item (field)
>     │         ^
>     = value `2147483648` does not fit into `INT4` (range: -2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647)
> 
> note: column `field` is of type `INT4`
> 
> help: reduce the value, change the column type to a wider type or change the overflow policy
